34 1, 2026]: Sec. 7. (a) As used in this section, "sweepstakes game"
35 means a game, contest, or promotion that:
36 (1) is available on the Internet;
37 (2) is accessible on a mobile phone, computer terminal, or
38 similar access device;
39 (3) utilizes a dual-currency or multi-currency system of
40 payment allowing a player to exchange currency for:
41 (A) a cash prize, a cash award, or cash equivalents; or
42 (B) a chance to win a cash prize, a cash award, or cash
EH 1052—LS 6389/DI 137

12
1 equivalents; and
2 (4) simulates:
3 (A) lottery games; or
4 (B) casino-style gaming, including slot machines, video
5 poker, table games, bingo, or sports wagering.
6 However, the term does not include a game, contest, or promotion
7 offered by the state lottery commission or peer to peer skill-based
