6 SECTION 37. IC 7.1-5-6-3, AS AMENDED BY P.L.32-2019,
7 SECTION 14, IS AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
8 JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 3. (a) It is unlawful for a person to act as a clerk
9 in a package liquor store, or as a bartender, waiter, waitress, security,
10 bouncer, or manager for a retailer permittee unless that person has
11 applied for and been issued the appropriate permit. This section does
12 not apply to dining car or boat employees, to a person described in
13 IC 7.1-3-1.7, or to a person described in IC 7.1-3-18-9(d). A person
14 who knowingly or intentionally violates this subsection commits a
15 Class C infraction. However, the violation is a Class B misdemeanor
16 if the person has a prior unrelated adjudication or conviction for a
17 violation of this section within the previous five (5) years.
18 (b) It is a defense to a charge under this section if, not later than
19 thirty (30) days after being cited by the commission, the person who
20 was cited produces evidence that the appropriate permit was issued by
21 the commission on the date of the citation.
22 (c) It is a defense to a charge under this section for a new applicant
23 for a permit if, not later than thirty (30) days after being cited by the
24 commission, the new applicant who was cited produces a receipt for a
25 cashier's check or money order showing that an application for the
26 appropriate permit was applied for on the date of the citation.
